<HEAD>Names in the News</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto NY14</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ARCATA, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ed Flanders, who played a compassionate
hospital administrator on television's ``St. Elsewhere,'' was
hospitalized in guarded condition after his car plunged down a
400-foot embankment, officials said.
   The 53-year-old actor was driving near the northern California
town of Salyer when his convertible left the road and went down the
hill Monday, said Highway Patrol Sgt. Vern Crogh. Flanders was
ejected from the car.
   He was taken to Mad River Community Hospital with head and chest
injuries and was in guarded condition in the intensive care unit
Tuesday, a nursing supervisor said.
   Flanders played the kind-hearted but self-righteous Dr. Donald
Westphall on ``St. Elsewhere.''
