<TEXT>
   Gov. Kay Orr says 31 years of marriage to
her husband, Bill, has been easier than being governor.
   The Republican governor chatted with reporters following the
dedication of a child care center.
   ``We're celebrating our 31st wedding anniversary today,'' she
told reporters Monday.
   Asked if it was easier being married that long or being
governor, Mrs. Orr, who was elected in 1986, laughed and said,
``being married.''
   She said she received a special gift when members of a
retirement center's bell choir played and serenaded her at the
governor's mansion.
