<HEAD>Dollar Down, Stocks Up</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The dollar closed lower againt the Japnanese yen
Wednesday, while share prices moderately rose on the Tokyo Stock
Exchange.
   The dollar closed at 134.20 yen, down 0.38 yen from the previous
day's close of 134.58 yen. After opening higher at 134.70 yen, the
currency traded between 134.20 and 134.75 yen.
   The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues, a 165.81-point
winner Tuesday, gained another 252.45 points or 0.92 percent to
close at 27,752.01. On Tuesday, the index cloed at 27,499.56 points.
   ``The market's doing even better than yesterday (Tuesday), and
investors are actively trading a variety of issues, in addition to
big ones such as steels and real estate,'' said a dealer with Daiwa
Securities in Tokyo.
   Trading had picked up considerably since Tuesday, the first day
of the new fiscal year for most Japanese companies, said the
dealer, speaking on condition of anonymity.
   Dealers attributed the dollar's higher opening rate to the
currency's strength overnight in the United States. They said a
lack of fresh market-affecting news also stabilize the dollar.
