<HEAD>Mafia Boss And Wife Killed In Murder Spree</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PALERMO, Sicily (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Gunmen burst into a villa today and
killed a Mafia boss and his wife, authorities said. The deaths were
the latest in a spree of gangland murders on the island.
   The killers struck around 11:30 a.m., shooting Giovanni Bontade
and his wife, Francesca, both 42, police said.
   Bontade was a defendant in the mass trial of more than 400 Mafia
suspects and was sentenced in December to eight years in prison for
criminal association. He was under house arrest pending an appeal.
   Bontade's brother, Stefano, was killed in 1981 in a war between
Mafia families.
   The killings bring to 10 the number of people slain in Sicily
this week. The victims include a prominent judge who presided over
two major trials of organized crime suspects and a well-known
leftist who campaigned against drugs and the Mafia.
   Investigators believe the killings are part of a new series of
Mafia attacks on the state, as well as a battle between rival gangs.
