<HEAD>Braille Schedules for Blind Sports Fans</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Blind sports fans can keep track of their
favorite teams with sports schedules being issued in Braille, the
Library of Congress said Wednesday.
   The library is producing Braille schedules for the National
Football League, National Hockey League, National Basketball
Association, Major Indoor Soccer League and the American and
National baseball leagues.
   The schedules are put into Braille form as they become available
throughout the year.
   Interested persons can obtain the schedules by calling
1-800-424-8567 or writing the National Library Service for the
Blind and Physically Handicapped, Library of Congress, Washington,
D.C., 20542.
