<1ST_LINE>r w AM-US-Israel-Bullets     09-28 0134</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-US-Israel-Bullets,130</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>US Troubled by Use of Plastic Bullets</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The State Department said Wednesday it is
disturbed by Israel's use of plastic bullets against Palestinian
demonstrators, contending that the policy is leading to rising
casualties in the occupied territories.
   According to published reports, at least three Palestinians have
been killed and 70 wounded since the Israeli Army began using
plastic bullets a month ago. The bullets have been described by
their defenders as non-lethal.
   ``We believe that measures must be taken to reduce rather than
to increase casualties among Palestinian demonstrators,'' State
Department spokeswoman Phyllis Oakley said.
   ``Thus we are disturbed by the rising casualties of Palestinians
in recent clashes with the Israeli military. We can see no
justification for a policy admittedly designed to cause an increase
in casualties.''
</TEXT>
