<1ST_LINE>r i AM-Germany-Escape     09-28 0212</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Germany-Escape,0218</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Border Guards Fire on Two Men Fleeing to West</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BERLIN (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Communist East German border guards shot at two
men who scaled the Berlin Wall to flee to the West on Wednesday,
and they arrested a woman accompanying the men, police said.
   The men escaped uninjured into West Berlin, said a West Berlin
police spokesman who spoke on condition of anonymity.
   Police said the woman was arrested by the East Berlin guards
after she fell while running and hurt herself.
   The incident came two days after the three allied powers in West
Berlin issued a protest note condemning the use of force in
preventing an escape attempt Sunday night.
   In another incident, East Berlin border guards fired warning
shots Sunday night to stop two men racing to scale the
heavily-fortified wall that divides the city. They were arrested,
but police said they were not injured.
   In Monday's protest note, signed by the United States, France
and Britain, the allies condemned the shooting as a ``violation of
basic human rights'' and an ``affront against the values of
civilized society.''
   The West German government and the West Berlin Senate
immediately condemned Wednesday's incident.
   More than 322 people people have fled East Germany to West
Berlin or West Germany this year.
</TEXT>
