   Seoul's tough-talking student radicals are threatening to
disrupt Sunday's marathon. A U.S. security specialist says his
biggest worry is the anti-Americanism surfacing among ordinary
South Koreans.
   One Korean official finds the real security threat coming from
the athletes themselves _ one might defect and put the Olympic
hosts in an awkward position.
