<1ST_LINE>r f PM-TreasuryAuction     09-28 0099</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Treasury Auction,0103</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Yields Down on Two-Year Treasury Notes</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Yields on two-year Treasury notes fell in the
government's latest auction to the lowest level since July.
   The average yield was 8.53 percent on Tuesday, down from 8.72
percent at the last comparable auction on Aug. 23.
   It was the lowest rate since two-year notes averaged 8.41
percent on July 27. The notes will carry a coupon interest rate of
8{ percent, with each $10,000 in face value selling for $9,994.60.
   A total of $8.78 billion in notes were sold out of bids
totalling $30.3 billion.
</TEXT>
