<HEAD>Stock Prices Rise Again In London, But Modestly</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: UPDATES throughout with close.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Prices closed modestly higher on the London Stock
Exchange Wednesday after an uneventful session.
   The gain failed to match Tuesday's jump, which followed news
that Britain's August trade deficit was lower than expected.
   Brokers said technical factors played a part in putting the
brakes on Wednesday as the market found it difficult to break
through the 1,820 points level.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-stock index ended 4.5
points, or 0.24 percent, higher at 1,815.5.
   Volume was 418.3 million shares, down from the 461.5 million
traded Tuesday.
   Traders said there was nothing in the news to sustain a strong
follow-through to Tuesday's rise.
