   The stock market held steady in quiet trading
today, still deadlocked over the outlook for interest rates and the
economy.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials rose 1.95 to 2,084.28 by
2 p.m. on Wall Street.
   Losers held a narrow edge on gainers in the overall tally of New
York Stock Exchange-listed issues, with 625 up, 642 down and 587
