<1ST_LINE>r f AM-Knight-Ridder-Tribune     09-28 0179</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Knight-Ridder-Tribune,0189</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Knight-Ridder and Tribune To Expand News Service</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Knight-Ridder Inc. and Tribune Co. announced
plans Wednesday to expand their joint supplemental news service
with a photo wire, a merged graphics service and a new wire for
smaller newspapers.
   Beginning Oct. 1, the KNT News Wire will be known as
Knight-Ridder-Tribune News Information Services.
   The Washington, D.C.-based service will become the first
supplemental news service to offer both electronic graphics and
daily black and white and color photos to subscribing newspapers,
the companies said.
   Through the merger of graphics services, Tribune graphics that
used to be mailed will be offered via the Knight-Ridder electronic
network.
   The new wire service for small and medium-size newspapers is
known as Select and will include a variety of news, sports,
entertainment and other material, the companies said.
   Coverage of business, entertainment and lifestyles also will be
expanded on the main wire.
   The service goes to more than 200 newspapers besides the 30
owned by Knight-Ridder and nine owned by Tribune Co., said Walter
Mahoney, vice president for sales.
</TEXT>
