<1ST_LINE>r f AM-BethlehemSteel     09-28 0094</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Bethlehem Steel,0099</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Steelmaker Adopts Poison Pill</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BETHLEHEM, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Bethlehem Steel Corp. said Wednesday its
directors approved a shareholders' rights plan, commonly known as a
poison pill, to discourage unwanted takeovers.
   Chairman Walter Williams said the board not aware of any plan to
acquire control of the company.
   Should a person or group launch a tender offer or acquire 20
percent of Bethlehem's outstanding common shares, the rights plan
would enable shareholders to tie up blocks of stock and thereby
dilute the raider's holdings.
   The plan will expire in 10 years.
</TEXT>
